@page "/about-me"

<h1>About ResumeAligner</h1>

<p>
    <strong>ResumeAligner</strong> is a web application designed to help users align their resumes with specific job descriptions, making it easier to tailor applications and improve job search outcomes. The app allows users to upload their resumes and job descriptions, then analyzes and matches relevant skills, experience, and keywords to provide actionable feedback.
</p>

<h2>Features</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Upload and parse resumes and job descriptions</li>
    <li>Automated matching and analysis of resume content</li>
    <li>Feedback and suggestions for improving resume alignment</li>
    <li>Intuitive navigation and user-friendly interface</li>
</ul>

<h2>Technologies Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>.NET 9</strong> and <strong>C# 13.0</strong> for backend and application logic</li>
    <li><strong>Blazor Server</strong> for interactive, real-time web UI</li>
    <li><strong>Entity Framework Core</strong> with SQLite for data storage</li>
    <li><strong>Bootstrap 5</strong> for responsive and modern styling</li>
</ul>

<p>
    ResumeAligner is built to streamline the resume tailoring process, leveraging modern web technologies to deliver a seamless and effective user experience.
</p>
